## Decision: Return `std::optional<T>`

### Rationale

| Return Strategy | Correctness | Ergonomics | Performance |
|-----------------|-------------|------------|-------------|
| `std::optional<T>` | ✓ Explicit empty state | Best (idiomatic C++17) | Zero overhead vs manual |
| `bool` + out-parameter | ✓ Works | Verbose, error-prone | Slightly more awkward API |
| `throw exception` | ✗ Empty queue is NOT exceptional | Poor (exceptions are slow) | High overhead on empty |

